A prototype of this study’s translator is currently hosted with Firebase and can be accessed via a
RESTful API. By turning it into a RESTful API instead of a hosted web application, any developer who wishes to
take advantage of this translator and incorporate it into other applications may do so. A translator of this nature
is of little use by itself but paired with a chat application or a social media platform where users across the
world will congregate to communicate with each other, it would be a step in the right direction towards helping
users understand each other a little better across language and cultural barriers.
